Reasoning: The paper proposes a deep learning approach for image restoration from under-sampled k-space data, which is a common problem in medical imaging. The use of deep learning and domain adaptation techniques suggests that the paper belongs to the computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The paper also discusses the use of x-ray computed tomography (CT) data, which falls under the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. The use of MR datasets suggests that the paper may also belong to the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category. Finally, the use of pre-training and fine-tuning techniques suggests that the paper may also belong to the neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) sub-category.
